President Obama has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Final Match of the 2014 FIFA World Cup in Brazil. The delegation will be led by Deputy Secretary of State Heather Higginbottom and includes United States Ambassador to Brazil Liliana Ayalde, Assistant to the President Jonathan McBride, CEO of The Hershey Company John P. Bilbrey, and former U.S. Men's World Cup player Cobi Jones.